  "prompt": "Why are upload speeds to Gmail so slow for attachments?",
  "response": "Slow upload speeds to Gmail when attaching files can be caused by several factors. Here are some common reasons and potential solutions:\n\n### 1. **Internet Connection Speed**\n   - Your upload speed is typically slower than your download speed, especially on asymmetrical connections like DSL or cable.\n   - **Solution**: Test your internet speed using tools like [Speedtest](https://www.speedtest.net). If the upload speed is significantly slower than expected, contact your ISP.\n\n### 2. **File Size**\n   - Large attachments take longer to upload, especially if your connection has a low upload speed.\n   - **Solution**: Compress files or split them into smaller parts before uploading.\n\n### 3. **Network Congestion**\n   - If multiple devices or applications are using your network, it can slow down upload speeds.\n   - **Solution**: Reduce network usage by pausing downloads, streaming, or other bandwidth-intensive activities.\n\n### 4. **Google Servers or Gmail Limitations**\n   - Gmail has a 25 MB attachment limit for emails. Larger files are automatically uploaded to Google Drive, which might introduce delays.\n   - **Solution**: Upload large files to Google Drive first and share the link in your email.\n\n### 5. **Browser or App Performance**\n   - Outdated browsers or poor-performing email clients can slow down uploads.\n   - **Solution**: Ensure your browser or app is up to date. Try using a different browser or the Gmail mobile app.\n\n### 6. **VPN or Proxy**\n   - Using a VPN or proxy can slow down upload speeds due to additional routing and encryption.\n   - **Solution**: Temporarily disable the VPN or proxy to see if it improves speed.\n\n### 7. **Firewall or Antivirus Software**\n   - Security software can sometimes interfere with upload speeds.\n   - **Solution**: Temporarily disable the firewall or antivirus to check if it\u2019s causing the issue. Add exceptions for Gmail if necessary.\n\n### 8. **Wi-Fi Signal Strength**\n   - Weak Wi-Fi signals can reduce upload speeds.\n   - **Solution**: Move closer to the router or use a wired connection for better stability.\n\n### 9. **Google Account or Server Issues**\n   - Temporary issues with Gmail or Google\u2019s servers could cause slow uploads.\n   - **Solution**: Check [Google\u2019s Workspace Status Dashboard](https://www.google.com/appsstatus) for any reported outages or issues.\n\n### 10. **Your Device\u2019s Performance**\n   - Slow processing power or insufficient RAM on your device can affect upload speeds.\n   - **Solution**: Restart your device and close unnecessary applications to free up resources.\n\nBy identifying and addressing the specific cause, you should be able to improve your upload speeds to Gmail.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
